&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Both of those returned &quot;404 Not Found&quot; with Solr 8.6.3.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not a Java developer, but I think it&apos;s a safe bet that the changes for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-14659&quot; title=&quot;Remove restlet from Solr&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;SOLR-14659&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-14659&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; have something to do with this.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="17273918" author="thomascorthals" created="Thu, 28 Jan 2021 18:18:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Prodding around in the code a bit, I noticed that HEAD doesn&apos;t get SCHEMA_READ_PERM like GET does. This is just a shot in the dark for me, haven&apos;t tested it.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nobr&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/attachment/13019579/13019579_0001-Same-PermissionName-for-HEAD-requests-as-for-GET-req.patch&quot; title=&quot;0001-Same-PermissionName-for-HEAD-requests-as-for-GET-req.patch attached to SOLR-15116&quot;&gt;0001-Same-PermissionName-for-HEAD-requests-as-for-GET-req.patch&lt;sup&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;rendericon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/link_attachment_7.gif&quot; height=&quot;7&quot; width=&quot;7&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/sup&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
